        <mxCell id="notesTitle" value="Key notes" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#424242;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="100" y="894" width="400" height="22" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="notesBody" value="&#8226;&#160;The enum values (1..14) are assigned in a different order than the detection priority. Row order above = detection order; the number after each name = enum value declared in the source.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226;&#160;Orange rows (kStandardType, kStreamType) are near the end: kStandardType wins for trivial POD types; kStreamType is checked last and only matches non-POD types with bidirectional stringstream operators.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226;&#160;Deduction runs entirely at compile time; runtime dispatch is a zero-cost switch typically eliminated by inlining.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226;&#160;If kUnknownType is returned, every Node fails its static_assert(is_supported(kMsgType))." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;fontSize=11;fontColor=#455a64;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="100" y="920" width="1000" height="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
